From 408aa0dd466594d5501190c32de4297359308579 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Riff <r12f.code@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2026 01:24:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat: implement init_writes and pre_poll support for
 I2C/SPI/I3C collectors (#156)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Add WriteStep config with I2C/I3C (address+value) and SPI (command) variants
- Add ByteValue type supporting single u8 or list<u8> deserialization
- Validate: reject on Modbus, address+value co-requirement, non-empty bytes, delay ≤ 10s
- Add MetricWriter trait with execute_writes() method
- Implement MetricWriter for I2C, SPI, and I3C protocols
- Add MetricWriterFactory and MetricFactory combined trait
- Execute init_writes at startup and after every reconnect
- Execute pre_poll before each read cycle; skip cycle on failure
- 3 consecutive pre_poll failures trigger reconnect with init_writes re-execution
- Add 12 unit tests for config parsing and validation of write steps
